# Important Points

- A method can call another method.
- A method can have zero or many parameters.
- A method can return only one value.
- `void` methods do not return anything.
- Non-void methods must return a value on every execution path.
- Parameters are local variables.
- Methods improve readability and code reuse.
- Static methods can be called directly from `main()`.

